OL,6,FSince then, economic circumstances
OL,7,Fhave deteriorated, with inflation
OL,8,Fproving higher than expected,
OL,9,Fborrowing costs increasing and the
OL,10,FOffice for Budget Responsibility
OL,11,Fexpected to downgrade its growth
OL,12,Fprojections after reviewing its
OL,13,Fapproach to forecasting productivity
OL,14,Fimprovements.
OL,16,FThe Government has also committed to a
OL,17,Fnumber of spending increases,
OL,18,Fincluding partially reversing cuts to
OL,19,Fthe winter fuel allowance, and is
OL,20,Fexpected to announce the lifting of
OL,21,Fthe two-child benefit cap.
