OL,3,CChancellor urged not to raise taxes on
OL,4,C'drained' businesses in Budget
OL,6,FShadow chancellor Sir Mel Stride said
OL,7,Fthe Chancellor did not need to raise
OL,8,Ftaxes again, but instead needed to get
OL,9,Fa grip on spending and, in particular,
OL,10,Fthe "spiralling welfare bill".
OL,12,FHe said: "Businesses need certainty,
OL,13,Fbut all they have from this Labour
OL,14,FGovernment is constant speculation
OL,15,Fabout damaging tax rises."
OL,17,FMs Haviland acknowledged that the
OL,18,FBCC's requests were "no small asks",
OL,19,Fbut added that if the Budget could
OL,20,F"deliver", the promise of stronger
OL,21,Fgrowth "can finally become reality".
